<subSubSection id="C30798E0FFEEA13DD791444FAC03FA2F" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA2CB6BFFEEA13DD791444FAC03FA2F" blockId="23.[151,1437,1183,2037]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFEEA13DD791444FA86CFAF7" bold="true" box="[199,321,1327,1352]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species differs from all other known Neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB0E8FFEEA13DD4B6444FAD64FAF7" box="[992,1097,1327,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFEEA13DD4B6444FAD64FAF7" box="[992,1097,1327,1352]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">Stigmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the female genitalia by the combination of a very large accessory sac, small corpus bursae with indictinctive comb-like pectinations, and large pointed anterior apophyses. The host-plant 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB0E8FFEEA13DD52A4417AA7CFA2F" box="[636,849,1399,1424]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conferta">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFEEA13DD52A4417AA7CFA2F" box="[636,849,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">Baccharis conferta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also makes this species highly distinctive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30798E0FFEEA13DD79144FCABC7F84B" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA2CB6BFFEEA13DD79144FCA8A5FA0A" blockId="23.[151,1437,1183,2037]" box="[199,392,1436,1461]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFEEA13DD79144FCA829FA0A" bold="true" box="[199,260,1436,1461]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA2CB6BFFEEA13DD79144DFAD4EF99F" blockId="23.[151,1437,1183,2037]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFEEA13DD79144DFA833FA67" bold="true" box="[199,286,1471,1496]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFEEA13DD66644DFA8B8FA67" box="[304,405,1471,1496]" captionStart="FIGURES 97 – 103" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1811,1834]" captionTargetBox="[248,1362,194,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 97 – 103. Stigmella confertae Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 97, 99, habitat, páramo, 10 km W of Papallacta, Napo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3700 – 3800 m; 98, host-plant Baccharis conferta Kunth; 100 – 102, leafmines; 103, forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261805/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD63144A0A8B8FA67" box="[359,405,1472,1496]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="103.0">103</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head: frontal tuft ochre; collar and scape cream; antenna longer than half the length of forewing; flagellum with 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD6E34484A8D7FA43" box="[437,506,1508,1532]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="27.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="27.0">27–28</number>
segments (n= 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD5CC4484AB84FA43" box="[666,681,1508,1532]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="2.0">2</number>
), fuscous. Thorax and tegula fuscous. Forewing unicolorous (fascia indistinct or absent; see Remarks), fuscous with purple iridescence. Abdomen fuscous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA2CB6BFFEEA13DD791474CADD6F948" blockId="23.[151,1437,1183,2037]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFEEA13DD791474CA8A6F9FA" bold="true" box="[199,395,1580,1605]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFEEA13DD6CC474CA8D1F9FB" box="[410,508,1580,1605]" captionStart="FIGURES 104 – 107" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,357,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[151,1436,339,1861]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 104 – 107. Stigmella confertae Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. and leaf-mines on Baccharis salicifolia. 104, female genitalia of S. confertae Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 638 (ZMUC); 105, 106, Baccharis salicifolia (Ruiz &amp; Pav.) Pers.; 107, leaf-mines of unknown Stigmella species on Baccharis salicifolia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261806/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD698474CA8D1F9FB" box="[462,508,1580,1604]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="104.0">104</number>
</figureCitation>
). Total length about 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD5B7474CAA26F9FA" box="[737,779,1580,1605]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="675.0">675</number>
µm. Abdominal apex broadly rounded, about 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD246474CAC5CF9FB" box="[1296,1393,1580,1604]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="115.0" valueMax="120.0" valueMin="110.0">110–120</number>
µm broad. Anterior and posterior apophyses almost equal in lenght; anterior apophyses very broad proximally, strongly narrowing (pointed) distally; posterior apophyses 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD59C4714AA07F932" box="[714,810,1652,1677]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="127.5" valueMax="145.0" valueMin="110.0">110–145</number>
µm long, very slender. Vestibulum very broad, without sclerites. Corpus bursae with folded distal part and with broader, oval-shaped, 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD37A47F7ADA3F90F" box="[1068,1166,1687,1712]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="262.5" valueMax="265.0" valueMin="260.0">260–265</number>
µm long, 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD25D47F7AC40F90F" box="[1291,1389,1687,1712]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="192.5" valueMax="205.0" valueMin="180.0">180–205</number>
µm broad, basal part, without signa; pectinations comb-like, indistintive, hardly visible (
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFEEA13DD31A47DCAD82F96B" box="[1100,1199,1724,1749]" captionStart="FIGURES 104 – 107" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,357,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[151,1436,339,1861]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 104 – 107. Stigmella confertae Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. and leaf-mines on Baccharis salicifolia. 104, female genitalia of S. confertae Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide no. AD 638 (ZMUC); 105, 106, Baccharis salicifolia (Ruiz &amp; Pav.) Pers.; 107, leaf-mines of unknown Stigmella species on Baccharis salicifolia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261806/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD3D747DCAD82F96B" box="[1153,1199,1724,1748]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="104.0">104</number>
</figureCitation>
). Accessory sac very large, folded; ductus spermathecae slender, with one distinct, strongly chitinized plate-like structure.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA2CB6BFFEEA13DD7914664ABC7F84B" blockId="23.[151,1437,1183,2037]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFEEA13DD7914664A867F8A2" bold="true" box="[199,330,1796,1821]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">Bionomics.</emphasis>
Larvae mine in leaves (
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFEEA13DD5344664AA2EF8A3" box="[610,771,1796,1821]" captionStart="FIGURES 97 – 103" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1811,1834]" captionTargetBox="[248,1362,194,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 97 – 103. Stigmella confertae Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 97, 99, habitat, páramo, 10 km W of Papallacta, Napo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3700 – 3800 m; 98, host-plant Baccharis conferta Kunth; 100 – 102, leafmines; 103, forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261805/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
Figs 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD5CB4664AA2EF8A3" box="[669,771,1796,1820]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="101.0" valueMax="102.0" valueMin="100.0">100–102</number>
</figureCitation>
). Host-plant: 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB0E8FFEEA13DD4C94664ADEBF8A2" authority="Kunth" authorityName="Kunth" box="[927,1222,1796,1821]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conferta">
<emphasis id="B9691779FFEEA13DD4C94664AD5AF8A3" box="[927,1143,1796,1821]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">Baccharis conferta</emphasis>
Kunth
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB0E8FFEEA13DD3814664AC78F8A3" box="[1239,1365,1796,1820]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFEEA13DD2384664A99AF8FF" captionStart="FIGURES 97 – 103" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1811,1834]" captionTargetBox="[248,1362,194,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 97 – 103. Stigmella confertae Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 97, 99, habitat, páramo, 10 km W of Papallacta, Napo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3700 – 3800 m; 98, host-plant Baccharis conferta Kunth; 100 – 102, leafmines; 103, forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261805/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD7C14648A99AF8FF" box="[151,183,1832,1856]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="98.0">98</number>
</figureCitation>
). Larvae bright green with dark grey-green intestine and dark brown head; mine in early January (and judging on numerous vacant leaf-mines) also in December. Leaf-mine as a gallery strongly widening and contorted in distal third (therefore resembling a blotch) (
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFEEA13DD56B460FABF1F837" box="[573,732,1903,1928]" captionStart="FIGURES 97 – 103" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1811,1834]" captionTargetBox="[248,1362,194,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 97 – 103. Stigmella confertae Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 97, 99, habitat, páramo, 10 km W of Papallacta, Napo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3700 – 3800 m; 98, host-plant Baccharis conferta Kunth; 100 – 102, leafmines; 103, forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261805/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
Figs 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD5204610ABF1F837" box="[630,732,1904,1928]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="100.101">100, 101</number>
</figureCitation>
). Usually but not always the distal part of leaf-mine is in distal portion of the leaf-blade (
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFEEA13DD6EE46F4AB36F813" box="[440,539,1940,1965]" captionStart="FIGURES 97 – 103" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1811,1834]" captionTargetBox="[248,1362,194,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 97 – 103. Stigmella confertae Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 97, 99, habitat, páramo, 10 km W of Papallacta, Napo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3700 – 3800 m; 98, host-plant Baccharis conferta Kunth; 100 – 102, leafmines; 103, forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261805/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD6BB46F4AB36F813" box="[493,539,1940,1964]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="102.0">102</number>
</figureCitation>
). Black frass (
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFEEA13DD5EA46F4AA31F813" box="[700,796,1940,1965]" captionStart="FIGURES 97 – 103" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1811,1834]" captionTargetBox="[248,1362,194,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 97 – 103. Stigmella confertae Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 97, 99, habitat, páramo, 10 km W of Papallacta, Napo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3700 – 3800 m; 98, host-plant Baccharis conferta Kunth; 100 – 102, leafmines; 103, forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261805/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD5A746F4AA31F813" box="[753,796,1940,1964]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="101.0">101</number>
</figureCitation>
) filling most of gallery except in the final part. Old leafmines appear brownish cream, distinctive (
<figureCitation id="1326D7EEFFEEA13DD52B46D8ABCDF86F" box="[637,736,1976,2001]" captionStart="FIGURES 97 – 103" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1811,1834]" captionTargetBox="[248,1362,194,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1790]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 97 – 103. Stigmella confertae Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 97, 99, habitat, páramo, 10 km W of Papallacta, Napo Province, Ecuador, the equatorial Andes, elevation 3700 – 3800 m; 98, host-plant Baccharis conferta Kunth; 100 – 102, leafmines; 103, forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261805/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="124">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD5D94CFFEEA13DD5E446D8ABCDF86F" box="[690,736,1976,2000]" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" value="102.0">102</number>
</figureCitation>
). Larval exit slit on upper side of the leaf. Cocoon grey-ochre to ochre; length 
<quantity id="4CE5668EFFEEA13DD61B46BCA8BCF84B" box="[333,401,2012,2036]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, maximum width 1.5–1.6 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
